{"id":14361,"date":"2013-05-20T20:13:29","date_gmt":"2013-05-20T16:13:29","guid":{"rendered":"http:\/\/www.dailyhadithonline.com\/?p=14361"},"modified":"2025-03-16T13:54:49","modified_gmt":"2025-03-16T09:54:49","slug":"nifaq-enjoin-maruf-do-munkar","status":"publish","type":"post","link":"https:\/\/www.abuaminaelias.com\/dailyhadithonline\/2013\/05\/20\/nifaq-enjoin-maruf-do-munkar\/","title":{"rendered":"Hadith on Hypocrisy: Punishment for enjoining good, doing evil"},"content":{"rendered":"<p>Usamah ibn Zayd reported: The Messenger of Allah, peace and blessings be upon him, said, &#8220;<b>A man will be brought on the Day of Resurrection and be cast into the Hellfire, and his intestines will pour forth in Hell. He will go around them as a donkey around a millstone. The people of Hell will gather around him and say: What has happened to you? Were you not enjoining good and forbidding evil? He will say: Of course, I used to enjoin good but I did not practice it myself, and I used to forbid evil but I practiced it myself<\/b>.\u201d<\/p>\n<p>Source: S\u0323ah\u0323i\u0304h\u0323 al-Bukha\u0304ri\u0304 3267, S\u0323ah\u0323i\u0304h\u0323 Muslim 2989<\/p>\n<p>Grade: <b><i>Muttafaqun Alayhi\u00a0<\/i><\/b>(authenticity agreed upon) according to Al-Bukhari and Muslim<\/p>\n<p align=\"right\">\u0639\u064e\u0646\u0652 \u0623\u064f\u0633\u064e\u0627\u0645\u064e\u0629\u064e \u0628\u0652\u0646\u0650 \u0632\u064e\u064a\u0652\u062f\u064d \u0642\u064e\u0627\u0644\u064e \u0642\u064e\u0627\u0644\u064e \u0631\u064e\u0633\u064f\u0648\u0644\u064f \u0627\u0644\u0644\u064e\u0651\u0647\u0650 \u0635\u064e\u0644\u064e\u0651\u0649 \u0627\u0644\u0644\u064e\u0651\u0647\u064f \u0639\u064e\u0644\u064e\u064a\u0652\u0647\u0650 \u0648\u064e\u0633\u064e\u0644\u064e\u0651\u0645\u064e\u00a0\u064a\u064f\u0624\u0652\u062a\u064e\u0649 \u0628\u0650\u0627\u0644\u0631\u064e\u0651\u062c\u064f\u0644\u0650 \u064a\u064e\u0648\u0652\u0645\u064e \u0627\u0644\u0652\u0642\u0650\u064a\u064e\u0627\u0645\u064e\u0629